New IPHist Reports Hey there team! From now on, if you are going to report someone for ban evasion in which an IP History was used, please make sure to mark the gamemode as IPHist instead of lobby or any other gamemode which you may have used. This change is so that it not only looks more profesional when copying the punishment command (for JrMods+), but also in order to make sure that the proof attached to the report does not get included in the ban message. Remember that you must always include proof of a confirmation from a Sr.Mod or Manager that the player who you are reporting is indeed ban evading, whether it's said in game, in dms, or in Staff Requests. All and all, a small QoL improvement that we hope y'all enjoy! Kind regards, ~ Management Team (edited)

Rodagave 30/06/2022 2:49 AM
@everyone New Staff Punishments System Howdy everyone. After having discussed this idea with those who were present in the staff meeting, we have decided to implement this brand new system. Please make sure to read everything within this message. For the Helpers
From now on, every single Helper will be required to submit the evidence for their non-permanent IP-Bans in #submissions. Usually, if a Helper performs a non-permanent IP-ban, you would just gather the proof before punishing, and punish the player once you have uploaded the proof. You will keep on following this same system, with a minor modification.
After you as a Helper have performed a non-permanent ban with the respective evidence, you will be required to submit a punishment form and fill all of the blanks respectively.
For example, if you encounter a user advertising their social media, you will take a screenshot of the chat as you always have, and IP-Ban the player for the respective offense. After having punished the user, you will go to #submissions and create a punishment form for the ban you just applied.
This system will only be followed for the non-permanent bans. For the Trials
Every Trial will be required to create a form in #submissions for any warn and/or mute they perform within their first 2 weeks of having joined the team.
Once a Staff member has been a Trial for longer than 2 weeks, they will not be required to submit this form, though it will remain as optional, unless they are instructed to do otherwise by a member of the Management Team.
For all of those who are currently Trials, please make sure to follow this system for the upcoming 2 weeks.
Who will handle these submissions?
The Jr.Mods and above will be in charge of handling both the submissions from the Helpers and from the Trials. Y'all will be provided instructions on how to do so privately.
If you were to have any questions, please make sure to let us know! Kind Regards, ~ Management Team (edited)

tom 3/07/2022 10:58 PM
@here Important Notice | Issuing Bans Hello Everyone, we hope everyone is well & doing great. We have noticed lately that certain staff duties are not being performed up to the mark and hence need to be addressed. So we request each and every one of you to read this announcement carefully, to ensure that things are more properly handled from now on.
We'd like to remind all the Jr. Mods that they are required to attach evidence to the bans issued on any player whose playtime is more than 24 hours. This applies to players who are camping as well. Although for the players who have a playtime lower than 24 hours, you are not required to ban them with evidence but we recommend recording and keeping the evidence handy for future reference.
We've also noticed that players are being punished for invalid reasons such as o/, bye, cya ... etc. We would like to make it very clear that you have to punish the user only for the offence that they have committed and not for any troll or funny reason. For example, if a player is Ban evading, you must ban him for Ban Evading and not for bye. On a similar note, we've noticed staff members adding additional characters such as uwu, lol ... etc to the reason of some punishments. To encourage professionalism, we request you guys to not punish users for reasons such as Flood uwu or Ban Evading (Cya lol).
We also request staff members not to ban players for the reason: Cheating. Cheating is a very vague term which neither tells the player banned nor the staff member handling his/her appeal, what exactly the player was punished for. We'd like everyone to specify the cheats used by the player as the reason for his/her punishment.
Please note: If a punishment has not been issued correctly or it doesn't follow the points stated above, it'll be considered invalid and will be removed from the player's history. Kind regards, ~ Management Team

@here Staff Alert | How to use the new /status Hello everyone! o/ It's been some days now since the new /status feature was implemented. As no announcement was made regarding how we expect you all to use this, this message can serve that purpose! Each status has a small text attached to it whenever you hover your username in /staff, which players can also see. We want this to be as representative of your currently availability as possible! There are 4 statuses: Online
"Available to help"
When online, we expect the you to to able to answer players in a "fast" manner whenever these require assistance of any kind. It can be from spectating a certain player due to them possibly hacking, going to a gamemode where someone is spamming, or just a quick question about a rule! If you are unable to attend to the players in a somewhat fast manner, there's other statuses to have, listed below. Away
"Away from staff duties"
You may use this status as a means of simply wanting some time off for your staff duties, such as playing some bedwars with your buddies, or having some time for yourself. This means, no more /jv when playing with friends, please use Away! You must still be checking up whats going on in game with this status though, so doesn't matter if you're running around spawn, if someone breaks a rule and you see it, you must punish. You may also remain with this status if you'd like when you are Staff Away. (edited)
5:52 PM
@here Busy
"Currently unavailable to provide in-game support"
This status is for when you are mainly handling reports on the forums or anything that is staff related and you can't or won't switch from what you're doing at the moment to attend another matter. So, no more /jv whenever you're handling reports please! You may use this status when handling reports, checking up on discord reports, any rule breakers in a specific gamemode, or when screensharing (though for this last one, Invisible is still a viable option). Offline For this status, it's best whenever you are going to be spectating a hacker or checking up on a rule breaker that you do not want them knowing you're there, though it's better paired with /jv when doing so.
‚ÑπÔ∏è You can quickly switch statuses, more info in /status info
With this announcement, we hope everyone will get used to this new system within some days. It's awesome that most of you all are now ditching /jv, and it really improves how the players see the staff team! Even if there's some busy staff members, it still shows that the team is active and doing their duties, which is a big +! If y'all have any questions, please let us know in your team channels or in #staff_ontopic. Kind regards, ~ Management Team (edited)

@everyone Account Security | Mandatory 2FA Hello everyone! Starting from today, we're going to enforce that everyone here uses /2fa with their staff accounts. There's been some cases where players were able to access staff member's accounts, and the only way to protect against that is by either IP Whitelisting the account (only if you're really static) and by adding /2fa.
How do you add 2FA?
Here is a helpful video! https://streamable.com/7xdylm Don't worry, I've changed my secret code & the password was 1234 for the purpose of the video And here is a helpful step by step guide: ‚Ä¢ 1Ô∏è‚É£ Run the command /2fa enable ‚Ä¢ 2Ô∏è‚É£ Copy the secret code or open the link provided. ‚Ä¢ 3Ô∏è‚É£ Within your desired 2fa application (Authy for Desktops or Google Authenticator on phones), input the secret code or scan the QR code. ‚Ä¢ 4Ô∏è‚É£ Run the command /2fa confirm <CODE>, by putting the 6 digit code that you've been given. ‚Ä¢ 5Ô∏è‚É£ All done!
Extra Information ‚ÑπÔ∏è
Now, we get that this might be a bit annoying if you're super dyanmic, meaning your IP changes every day, or maybe multiple times a day, but spending an extra 10-15 seconds when logging in is better than someone outside of the team having access to a staff account. I don't think we have to mention the fact that you musn't share your secret code either, but just incase, now you know! We expect everyone to apply /2fa to your accounts within this week, although the sooner the better. So, now whenever you login, you'll not only need to type the usual /login <password> command, but also /2fa code <CODE>. If this code doesn't work, don't worry! Just wait for the next code to appear in ~30 seconds, and it should work. If this still doesn't work after many attempts, or you have any other qestions, please contact us through your Team Channel . Kind Regards, ~ Management Team (edited)

@everyone Staff Meeting | September 2022 Howdy everyone! It's been some months since we last had a General Staff Meeting, and it's about time we have another one!
What's a Staff meeting? What is the purpose?
Some of you might be new to staff meetings, and here is a quick and brief explanation of what goes on in them: The management team often announces some changes that will be occurring soon, and if you've got any feedback about anything regarding staff duties and the server in general, note them down as you can discuss it with the rest of the team here!
What will be talked about in this specific Meeting?
While we don't want to reveal everything just yet, we've got some cool stuff planned! Such as a way to introduce yourself to any new members of the team, so basically your own Staff Welcome message, and discussing what you've all written in your Staff Surveys. Something extra about the surveys too; Thank you a lot to everyone who found the time to put effort into it! Even some of you that were staff away still went out of your way to give us some amazing feedback, and it really helps. We are really glad how it turned out, and stay tuned on any future Surveys with different types of questions!
When is it? What if I can't make it or I don't want to join?
The meeting will be held on Saturday, 10 September 2022 4:00:00 PM, so that means it'll be 10/09/2022 4:00 PM. Now, while it isn't required to join the meeting, it's encouraged you do so, since you'll be able to be involved with what's talked about and listen to the news at the same time than the rest of the team! Something that is required however is for you to let us know in your team channels if you'll be able to make it or not. We hope to see you all there! Kind regards, ~ Management Team

@everyone IMPORTANT NOTICE | Staff Guidelines Modification Howdy Team. Today we are announcing some important changes directly related to everyone of y'all. These changes are mainly to focus on improving the way controversial scenarios are dealt with, and to ensure the rules of the Network are not only being applied correctly at all times, but that they also remain updated throughout time. The main aspect we'll describe are the staff guidelines. These include modifications in the way punishments are handled under controversial scenarios, the way punishments are lifted, amongst others.
‚ùì Controversial Scenarios: Lately, it has been pretty common, for controversial scenarios to be raised. These can include such as not knowing whether a sentence is punishable or not, not knowing whether a message falls under a specific rule, not knowing whether a punishment was falsely applied or not, amongst others. And it is no secret that due to these controversial scenarios, multiple arguments have occurred throughout the weeks due to the difference in opinions and points of view. This is why from now on we will be forwarding these scenarios to the members of the @deleted-role . As soon as a scenario involving the interpretation of a rule begins to create multiple opinions within a discussion, this issue will be the responsibility of those within the rules interpretation committee to look into, and therefore those previously involved in the discussion should leave it up to the already stated members (Unless you are a part of the committee). Having said this, if you are a part of a discussion involving a controversial scenario, and a member of the rules interpretation committee notifies you that the matter will be taken into their hands, please make sure to be patient.
Punishing for a Not-listed Detail Within a Rule: It has also been brought to our attention that many discussions have taken place because of the misunderstanding of a rule, the lack of information a rule provides, or even because the rule does not necessarily cover the aspects it should. Which is why from now on, these will be the responsibility of the members within the @deleted-role to handle. In order to ensure the rules of the Network are up-to-date, and fit the community in the best way possible, the members within the Quality Assurance Committee will be the ones responsible for looking after these. Therefore, if a member of this committee notices an on-going argument due to any of the stated reasons, they will forward this issue to the remaining members of the committee and solve it as soon as possible.
Lifting Punishments: We will be applying a modification to the punishment lifting process. Currently, every one of y'all is able to, and allowed to remove any of your partners' punishments against a user, although we have always encouraged discussion before doing so. Though, from now on this will no longer be the case: You will no longer be allowed to remove a punishment applied from a staff member above your rank, unless they let you do so, surely. If you are attempting to remove a punishment applied by a staff member with the same rank as you, you will be required to discuss the removal reason with them first. And, if you are attempting to remove a punishment from a staff member below your rank, you will be required to notify them of the reason for this removal. Previously, we encouraged y'all to share the removal reason, and we truly appreciate every single one of you who has followed this, but it will now be a requirement, following the respective rank requirements.
If any of you have any questions, please make sure to ask them right away, I will be more than glad to clear any doubts! Kind regards, ~ Rodagave

@everyone Coordinated Admissions Program (CAP) | Staff Admissions Greetings. We are excited to announce that we will be introducing a new program called the "Coordinated Admissions Program". This program is designed to help us identify and train strong staff applicants who are interested in joining our team, but who have not been granted immediate admission. The Coordinated Admissions Program is specifically aimed at those who we believe have great potential but need further training and development. It is our hope that by offering this program, we can provide these applicants with the support and resources they need to reach their full potential and become valuable members of our team. As part of this program, we will be inviting promising candidates to undergo a 1-month training program. During this time, they will have the opportunity to prove themselves and showcase their skills and dedication. However, we would like to highlight that as part of the program, candidates will be required to meet certain requirements on a weekly basis, and pass a series of tests to prove their knowledge. We believe that by offering this program, we can better evaluate each candidate's abilities, knowledge, and overall suitability for the role. We are committed to selecting the best candidates for the team, and this program will help us ensure that we are inviting qualified and dedicated members.
Note: It is worth to mention that after successful completion of this program, the member would immediately be admitted to the staff team under the Trial position. Though, their Trial period will be reduced from 4 weeks to 2 weeks, given how they have already undergone training sessions.
If you happen to have any questions, concerns, or suggestions, please let us know. Thank you. Kind regards ~ Rodagave

@here Screenshare Subgroup | Looking for members! Hello team! The Team Screenshare subgroup is currently looking for active members to aide in a big part of the staff team.
What is team screenshare?
Screensharing is a way of finding closet cheats, cheats that are not blatant enough to punish through video proof. Through a screenshare, we can check the suspected users PC to check for these type of cheats and ban them accordingly. It can also be used to find people who could be ban evading (as some of you might have noticed when requesting an IPHist). It's efficient, thorough, and reliable.
‚ÑπÔ∏è Team Screenshare responsibilities
Team screenshare is very different from other subgroups. To be accepted into this position you must be professional, respectful, dedicated, and trusted. Screensharing is a very serious matter, as you are having access to other users' PCs, which can harm their privacy. Everything must be kept confidential to keep our players safe.
‚ùìWhy should I join?
‚Ä¢ Team screenshare members are taught from scratch, no prior knowledge is needed. ‚Ä¢ The team is growing, and constantly collaborating with each other. No shame in asking any questions! ‚Ä¢ Working to keep the server clean from those pesky closet cheaters. ‚Ä¢ Special freeze permissions and logs that only team screenshare members have access to. ‚Ä¢ Screensharing is a useful skill which can be used outside of just finding cheats. You'll be more tech-savvy after learning. ‚Ä¢ Organized team with many resources. ‚Ä¢ If it gets enough growth, active members will be able to obtain extra credits than per usual.
Requirements:
‚Ä¢ Being able to have MC, AnyDesk and a Browser open while recording (exceptions can be made, such as closing the game). ‚Ä¢ Ability to record for long periods of time. Screenshares can last up to an hour. ‚Ä¢ Some knowledge of closet cheats / ban evasion. ‚Ä¢ Professionalism, respect, and trust. So, are you interested in joining?
Apply for the subgroup here: https://forms.gle/dwQtA29P6a72wmBv6 Ô∏è Note: If your application has not been reviewed in 24 hours, contact a Sr.Mod via your team channel.
Kind regards, ~ Management Team / Screenshare Administrators

@everyone Staff Team Colonies | Entertainment & Staff Incentives Good evening team. I hope you are all doing well. After having taken your feedback into consideration, you have all helped us better understand the importance of breaking the routine and perform more entertaining activities over time. It is due to this that we have strongly considered your idea of implementing a Staff SMP, and are glad to announce the following. After hours of hard-work and time put toward this project, we have completed the creation of the brand new Colony server! There is a lot of information that comes along with this project, but we surely do hope it can serve as a source of motivation, and eventually build stronger bonds between each one of us. Now, there is some highly important information that we must share with you all beforehand. We would like to highlight how this server will serve as nothing else but a perk and a benefit of being a part of the staff team - and as any benefit or perk, it can be removed. - Meet the weekly staff playtime and activity requirements. All of the information regarding this server has been shared within its discord server. We look forward to having fun with you all in the brand new server, and hope to see you there! @everyone Staff meeting | August 2023
What will be discussed during the staff meeting?
Well for some of you, this is your first staff meeting, staff meetings are called every 3 months in order for us, the management team, to explain some changes that we're gonna make to the team shortly as well as to gather feedback for these ideas, as well as asking for feedback in general and as always, suggestions.
How will it work?
We'll setup a text and voice channel in order for everyone to communicate, the management team will take charge in explaining the first few things and then ask for feedback, which can be shown from either text or voice, however in order to keep it non-chaotic, only one person may speak at a time.

If you're unable to attend, then please do ping us within your team channel to let us know that you aren't able to attend. This meeting is mandatory to those who are available. We'll end up posting a conclusion of the meeting at the end as well
The meeting will be held on Sunday, 6 August 2023 5:00:00 PM
Kind regards, ~ Management Team

‚ùï @everyone Taking Ownership of Responsibilities | Important Reminder Greetings Team! It has recently come to our attention that while being totally dedicated towards punishing rule breakers, we often overlook the importance of making sure that every punishment we place has to be fair, valid, and properly communicated to the affected players. Let's remember that these punishments are placed on players who are putting time and effort into the server, and the purpose of placing punishments is to ensure everyone keeps playing while adhering to the rules. The management team does not oversee every single punishment that you issue to players, and that is what makes it all the more important for you to take full ownership of your responsibilities and exercise due diligence, making sure the punishment you place is on a fair and rational basis, and ask yourself whether you would accept such a punishment if it were placed on you on the same grounds. If a staff member or the punished player asks you about it or seeks clarification, you must always respond to them and ensure the punished player understands what they were punished for. While we already emphasize the importance of not ignoring the players, we should give extra attention to the punishments we, ourselves, place. Thank you for understanding, and keep up the good work. Kind Regards, ~ Management Team (edited)

@here General Staff Meeting January 2024's Summary ‚úçÔ∏è Hey there everyone! Thank you to all of you who participated in our last meeting! It was thrilling to see so many of you show up, and the high turnout was a clear representation of how big the team has gotten and how active it is. Here is the long-awaited summary of what occurred in the meeting: Gamemode Teams: Due to how well Team Factions has performed, we will be re-implementing Team Skyblock and Team Prison! We will be creating a Discord server for these groups and allowing community members to both get updates and participate in polls within those teams. Each team will be given a supervisor to take care of their respective gamemode team and ensure everything runs smoothly. More details on this update will be coming out soon. Subgroup Rework: Our subgroups lately have not been the best, and with how the team is currently going, we are looking to bring a significant update to them. This revamp will involve us implementing new guidelines and operations, as well as giving more leadership opportunities. Currently, we are working to revamp team Events and team Screenshare, which we know you all have been eagerly awaiting. Staff Reviews: We are considering re-implementing staff cards, which contain feedback and statistics for a given staff member. This would be a bit different from the system we had back in 2021. However, the purpose is still to motivate staff members and provide them feedback to improve on. Staff Home: With the departure of the Staff Site, we recognize the need for a new organizational hub. All documents related to ranks and subgroups will be placed on the forums for easy access. The Staff Home page will continue to be updated as we work on adding more features that were previously available on the Staff Site. Incentives: We are exploring ways to motivate everyone, especially in repetitive subgroup duties. This may include more staff competitions and events. If you have suggestions, please share them in your team channel or with me directly. These are some of the most important topics discussed during the meeting. As always, these plans may evolve, and we will provide a QOL update along with an official announcement when they are implemented. Kind regards, ~ Management Team

Rodagave 24/05/2024 3:52 AM
Hello team. I would like to communicate a message to y'all. My message will be discussing some details of the @Staff Away role. And whether you are or not away, please make sure to read my message. Recently, I have been reviewing multiple aspects of the staff team we can improve. This includes subgroups, some protocol issues, activity, incentives, etc. In our efforts to further improve the efficiency and the communication held within the staff team, I noticed a few issues with the @Staff Away role's usage. This role is only meant for a staff member to be displayed as away in the eyes of their partners and the community members so their assistance isn't requested for a short period of time. This role is only to be used if a staff member is going to be inactive for less than 2 months (there is no guide or document that states this at the time, this is why I am sharing this information right now). If a staff member is going away for over 2 months, we will start requesting resignations. Now, for those who are planning on going away for over 2 months, don't panic. If we request your resignation due to your away period length, we will share with you details on how to join the staff team without the need of reapplying or going through the Trial period again. Some of you may be given a window of 4 months to come back, or maybe even 8 - depending on your staff rank and how long you've been with us for. Whether you have things to do in life such as your job, school, or even a long vacation, we totally get it, but we are looking forward to have a team full of staff members we can rely on. And, if we, or your partners can not rely on you for 2 or more months, it's better for you to resign and join back once you are able to be active again. The same applies if you go away for less than 2 months but you go away once again as soon as you get back. If we notice an inconsistency with your activity, we will highly likely request a resignation. And to make things clear, this is not because we are "kicking you out because you have a life", we are asking you to temporarily leave the staff team in good terms until you are able to be active again, because first, we would never expect you to put your duties before your life, and we also seek to keep the efficiency of the staff team.
3:54 AM
Adding on to this communication, if you do go away for less than 2 months, please do your best to keep us posted on your away status. We've had many instances before in which we are trying to keep track of someone's status and they do not reply for days or weeks. As you may understand, this isn't something we find to be ideal. If y'all have any questions, comments or concerns, let me know. Best regards, ~ Rodagave

Rodagave 16/07/2024 6:35 PM
Hello team. After having noticed multiple of you share this same concern, I'd like to share a not-so-brief communication with y'all to clarify any doubts and/or concerns y'all may have. As you all know, every staff recruitment process has been put on hold until further notice. And with this, many resignations also took place, which eventually lead to the concern of a lack of staff members being raised. It is totally understandable for y'all to be concerned about the lack of staff members. Nevertheless, this is all part of our goal to turn the staff team into a more enjoyable journey for everyone. The reason I paused all the recruitment processes is due to the many issues I noticed were present within the staff team. These including inactivity, lack of communication, lack of growth opportunities for the more experienced staff members, lack of true engagement, unorganized protocols and procedures, and more. All of these issues are much harder to look into with a staff count of over 40, with almost half of them being almost completely inactive. Due to this, I decided to request a resignation from all of them. Now that we are at a point where the majority of the team is active, rather than not, it grants us the opportunity to properly look into the issues that can be directly improved by us. Which is something I have been working hard on for the past few weeks along with the management team. Even though we don't have as many staff members as we had before, I am not concerned at all, because I know that we can know rely on the majority of the team, rather not being able to most of the time. On top of all of this, it wasn't fair for us to keep on recruiting staff members when we knew they wouldn't enjoy their journey as much, and would eventually resign sooner than later. This is why during this pause, we are looking into all of the aspects the new staff members go through, and improving them to make sure they go through a smoother and more enjoyable journey. If you guys have any questions regarding this message, please don't hesitate to tag me in any channel. Best regards, ~ Rodagave

‚ÑπÔ∏è Announcement | Key Performance Indicators | KPIs @everyone The Key Performance Indicators is a new system that will be implemented amongst the Network, that serves to make sure that we are constantly rising to meet the demands required. The KPI's will be supervised by the members of the Management Team. The system will be based around weekly statistics and/or activity that will be requested from every staff member to be accomplished, failing to do so will result in the staff member being considered inactive amongst the staff team. Inability or failure to meet numerous KPIs in a row will lead to a warning, which will further result in a forced resignation/demotion from the JartexNetwork Staff Team. The goal of the KPI's is to allow the Management Team to establish specific milestones for each individual member of the team, that will be expected to rise to meet on a weekly basis, and may change based on what is considered needed to improve on specific focus points for individual weeks. An example, the KPI for the following days may be, "Reach 250 messages within the main discord", and for the following it may be, "Comment under 10 different introduction posts on the forums". These tasks will be assigned with the goal in mind of making sure we are touching base on all aspects of the Network, instead of only a few or no staff members doing so. Any further questions about the KPI's may be directed in your team channels or directly to a member of the Management Team. Kind regards, ~ Management Team

iFlyYT 20/12/2024 11:24 AM
@everyone Dismantlement of Recruitment Groups | Team Applications & Recruiting Committee As the new year approaches, we have gone to evaluate how we perform our recruitment process and because of that, we have decided to disband Team Applications and the Recruitment Committee. This is because it is difficult for members of both groups to know what the management team's goals are for a month, as well as what we're ideally looking for. Meaning that in the grand scheme of things, applicants that were previously denied may have been accepted with our aspirations in mind, and vice versa. This is at no fault of either groups, and it is much more effective to allow the Management Team to take charge of the recruitment process all together. However, we still value each and every single staff member's opinion and because of that, Trial Applications will now be accessible to Helpers and above. This is with the intention of hearing anyone's potential feedback about an applicant. Any feedback given will be taken into consideration when making our decision, as well as the goals that the management team has in mind. Our intention is not to limit the transparency between the staff team and the management team, considering everyone will be granted access to the applications sub-forum, but with the new year approaching, we aim to update some of our protocols to better suit the Network's needs. We thank both the Applications team and the Recruitment Committee for all of the hard work they have done during their lifespan. Best regards, ~ Management Team

@everyone Management Departments | Information & Updates Hello everyone. The purpose of this announcement is to officially introduce a specific concept of the management team publicly. For the past few months, you may have noticed some Sr.Mods being more involved in certain aspects than others, and after having followed this system for a few months, I would like to properly communicate it with you all. The way the management team works as of right now is the following; The management team is split into 5 different departments, these being Operations, Risk Management, Staff Development, Community Relations, and lastly, Innovation and Strategy. The departments allow for the management team to hold each other accountable for handling their responsibilities and tasks, given that each department is lead by one Sr.Mod, hence the 5 current Sr.Mods. Let me provide y'all with a quick rundown of each department.
Operations - Department Head: @iFlyYT - Summary: Oversee the day-to-day management and staff operations, and ensure both teams are conducing their duties according to the standard procedure.
Risk Management - Department Head: @Bene_e - Summary: Mitigate risks, ensure every member of the management and staff teams are abiding by the code of conduct, investigate, document, and issue disciplinary actions accordingly.
Staff Development - Department Head: @Flappix786 - Summary: Review staff members' performance, ensure proper execution of the mentorship program and with this, ensure proper training of mentees, as well as handle promotions.
Community Relations - Department Head: @KeylessSeal 🔑 👅👅👅👅 - Summary: Ensure the management and staff teams maintain a strong rapport with members of the community, collect and distribute feedback accordingly, and build a stronger rapport with the community over time.
Strategy & Innovation - Department Head: @rexxmidle - Summary: Review potential updates to already existent systems/procedures/protocols, evaluate areas of improvement, and implement changes accordingly.
New Awards & Recognitions - Department Head: Vacant - Summary: Review staff members' and management members' performance, share periodic feedback, assist staff members in the overall growth opportunities, and acknowledge the staff members' efforts if meeting or exceeding expectations.
I hope this brings some clarity to y'all's minds. If y'all have any questions related to any department, feel free to tag me or the department head in your channels. Best regards, Rodagave

iFlyYT 10/03/2025 11:01 PM
@here Polar Reports System | Clarifications During this new update, we had gotten a few questions from the staff team, let us answer them the following: ‚ùì Should we apply a tag ( for e.g. [FR]) to the /reports?
Yes, apply the [PS] tag for each punishment, both for chat and gameplay reports. PS stands for Polar System and allows us to reference where the report came from, especially in the context of chat punishments.
‚ùì What offense ladder should we use for chat offenses?
Use the normal offense, not the forum/discord reports offense! The reason that we have such offenses for those platforms is due to that it is incovninient for players to report, and that we miss many messages being reported. With this new update, that should no longer be a major issue
‚ùì Can we share chat logs URLs or screenshots?
No. These are considered confidential for a number of reasonings, and is required to be kept private that they even exist. However, you can reference to the player on what they did (for e.g. stating that they had said racial slurs on the KitPvP gamemode at 10 PM GMT)
We hope this clears everything up! Kind regards, ~ Management Team

@everyone Staff Replies | Appeals, One Stop, Trial Applications, Player Reports Hello everyone! We are implementing a new feature that allows staff members to reply to threads with only staff visibility! This means that you can post a reply and only staff members would be able to see it. This feature is intended to improve the communication between staff members as well as to add notes on specific cases Please keep in mind the following:
  • Keep everything on topic: no conversations, only information/intel that is absolutely relevant to the specific thread
  • Add whatever information you can as a staff reply instead of replying on Discord to ensure all information is logged to that thread
  • Ideally add everything to one singular reply, rather than 10 replies # How do I use this feature?
In order to use this feature, head to a thread and click "Staff-Only" and click "Post Reply"!

Use Cases:

Appeals

  • Provide information on your bans for others who are handling the appeal
  • Reply to the thread when you are handling the appeal (ensure to set Appeal Revision too)
  • Add any extra information such as awaiting staff request to be replied to
  • Linking evidence (ECCI types) to appeals when necessary ### One Stop Support Tickets
  • Current status of the ticket
    • For example you may look into a false ban and you could put a reply as "Contacted iFlyYT to investigate the validity of false ban - awaiting reply of iFlyYT"
    ### Trial Applications
  • Provide your thoughts and opinions on an applicant
    • Please keep in mind to only suggest your opinion; it is not to discuss other's opinions!
    ### Player Reports
  • Status of the report (for example awaiting staff request, or other staff opinions)
  • Providing any extra information such as suspected of it being a faked report
